# TypeScript + Tailwind

## Project structure

- `src/app/` — routes, layouts, global styles
- `src/components/` — reusable UI
- `src/lib/` — data access, utilities, env helpers
- `src/types/` — shared TypeScript types

## TypeScript

- Use explicit types for props, MongoDB documents, and serialized API shapes.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; use `type` for unions and mapped types.
- Import types with `import type` when values are not needed.
- Validate external input at boundaries (`src/lib/env.ts`, search query handling).

## Tailwind CSS v4

- Global theme tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme inline`).
- Use utility classes in components; match the existing dark zinc/amber palette.
- Keep layouts responsive with standard breakpoints (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`).
- Fonts are loaded in `layout.tsx` via `next/font` CSS variables (`--font-geist-sans`).

## Styling patterns

- Dark background: `bg-zinc-950`, text: `text-zinc-100`, accents: `text-amber-400`.
- Use semantic HTML (`header`, `main`, `section`) with accessible contrast.
- Avoid inline styles unless Tailwind cannot express the rule cleanly.

## Code quality

- Follow ESLint (`eslint-config-next`) and existing naming conventions.
- Minimize comments; prefer clear names over explanatory noise.
- Reuse existing components and lib helpers before adding new abstractions.
